abstract: >-
  Benchmark dataset, validation execution reports, and reproducer scripts
  for the FAVES V4 paper. FAVES V4 is a four-layer cheminformatics screening
  system aligned to the U.S. HHS/ASTP/ONC FAVES rubric (Fair, Appropriate,
  Valid, Effective, Safe) for trustworthy AI in healthcare. This release
  contains the full v3 ground truth (102 compounds), the V4 field-completeness
  200-compound set, the validation execution record (362/362 post-fix), the
  cross-RDKit-version external reproducibility report (20/20), and the
  end-to-end latency benchmark (90 steady-state samples). The seven NMCP-FAVES
  governance documents are summarized in Section 4 of the manuscript; full
  operational versions are available from the corresponding author.
keywords:
  - cheminformatics
  - structural alerts
  - PAINS
  - BOILED-Egg
  - controlled substances
